headline: Healthpeak (DOC) Beats Q4 FFO and Revenue Estimates
summary: Healthpeak (DOC) delivered FFO and revenue surprises of +3.37% and +2.84%, respectively, for the quarter ended December 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: Healthpeak: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The Denver-based real estate investment trust said it had funds from operations of $331.7 million, or 47 cents per share, in the period. The average estimate of five analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of 46 cents per share. Funds from operations is a closely watched measure in the REIT industry.

headline: Healthpeak Properties Provides Strategic Initiatives Update and Reports Fourth Quarter 2025 Results
summary: DENVER, February 02, 2026--Healthpeak Properties, Inc. (NYSE: DOC), a leading owner, operator, and developer of real estate for healthcare discovery and delivery, today provided a strategic initiatives update and announced results for the quarter ended December 31, 2025.

headline: AI Capex Clouds The Tech Horizon, Even As Meta And Tesla Shine
summary: On Thursday, Nasdaq fell 1.3% as the market digested mixed results from some Mag 7 reports. The primary weight came from Microsoft. AI spending anxiety rippled through the software sector.
